# Human Quality Filter

> *Memory compounds correct and incorrect beliefs equally — human discussion is the quality filter.*  
> — Bryan Lawrence, VALUExBRK 2026 (Oakcliff Marvin/Vicki)

## Rules

- **Never** edit `_system/memory/MEMORY.md` during agent sessions
- **Never** mark findings FINAL without a file in `_system/reviews/approved/`
- Propose beliefs only as `[PROPOSED]` or `[PROPOSED MEMORY]` in `_system/memory/daily/{date}.md`
- Tag proposed beliefs by genius: `[PROPOSED MUNGER]`, `[PROPOSED PABRAI]`, `[PROPOSED STAHL]`, `[PROPOSED MOI]`, or `[PROPOSED COMPANY]`
- Log agent errors to `_system/memory/corrections.md` before cross-check reports

## Memory taxonomy (`_system/memory/MEMORY.md`)

Human promotes approved beliefs into genius-specific sections:

- **Charlie Munger** — mental models, inversion, psychology, moats, circle of competence, capital allocation
- **Mohnish Pabrai** — dhando, bet sizing, business selection, cloning, valuation heuristics, portfolio discipline
- **Murray Stahl** — croupier model, exchanges, real diversification, spinoffs, macro/pecuniary society, lifecycle
- **Company-specific** — ticker theses after deep dives
- **Portfolio context** — archetype mix, conviction tiers, diversification audit
- **MOI / idea generation** — inefficiency source, uses/misuses, special-situation discipline (after human promotion from `[PROPOSED MOI]`)

Source PDFs: `_system/reference/investment-wisdom/`

## Review pipeline

```
Marvin writes → {TICKER}/research/report.md
             → summary → _system/reviews/pending/
             → human reads + discusses
             → corrections → _system/memory/corrections.md
             → approved items → _system/memory/MEMORY.md
             → move review → _system/reviews/approved/
```

## Cross-check mode

When challenging external analysis: re-derive from `{TICKER}/` primary PDFs first. List agreements, disagreements, missing data, then **Synthesis (best estimate)** per `_system/frameworks/external_view_blend.md`. Do not end with binary Marvin-only vs external-only; produce a weighted middle and record in `valuation.json` `estimates` when material.

## Prompt templates

Use task templates in `_system/prompts/` (onboard, download-refresh, daily scan, deep-dive, cross-check). Prepend context from `_system/prompts/_prefix.md` when running Marvin tasks.
